Print a styled table for HTML or LaTeX output

print_table.Rd

This function prints a styled table either in HTML or LaTeX format based on the output document type.

print_table(
  df,
  caption = "",
  digits = 2,
  print_rownames = FALSE,
  fontsize = 9,
  big.mark = ",",
  na_str = "",
  ...
)

Arguments

df

The data frame to be formatted as a table.

caption

The caption for the table (default: ”).

digits

Number of digits to display (default: 2).

print_rownames

Logical indicating whether to print row names (default: FALSE).

fontsize

Font size for the table (default: 9).

...

Additional arguments to be passed to the formatting functions.

Value

A styled table either in HTML or LaTeX format.

Examples

head(mtcars)%>%print_table()
